    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix pthread stack size issue in tracer new_thread function\n\n### Summary\nThe `new_thread()` function in the tracer module was requesting an excessive stack size of 10MB which exceeds the typical 8MB system stack limit. This caused `pthread_attr_setstacksize()` to fail and prevented thread creation in the tracer GUI components.\n\nAdditionally, the function was calling `exit(1)` on pthread errors which would terminate the entire application rather than gracefully handling the thread creation failure.\n\nThe changes reduce the stack size to a more reasonable 2MB and improve error handling to prevent application crashes.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/utils.c`: \n  * Changed stack size from 10MB to 2MB to stay within system limits\n  * Replaced `exit(1)` calls with `return` statements for graceful error handling\n  * Added proper cleanup with `pthread_attr_destroy()` in error paths\n  * Added documentation comments explaining the stack size choice\n\n"
}